g": "united-kingdom"}], "biography": "Ralph Kemplen (8 October 1912 – 4 April 2004) was a British film editor with more than fifty film credits between 1933 and 1982. Kemplen had a long collaboration with director John Huston (1906-1987) on six films between 1951 and 1966. Kemplen also directed one feature film, The Spaniard's Curse (1958).Kemplen won the BAFTA Award for Best Editing for The Day of the Jackal (1973) and was nominated three times for the Academy Award for Best Film Editing (for Moulin Rouge (1952), Oliver! (1968), and Day of the Jackal).", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-06T00:19:33.386013+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 6119, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ralph_Kemplen"}], "uuid": "92bc9dd7-4b47-4c85-8dda-2c4e3c914bd5", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": null, "external_references": [{"id": 51085, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q1625282"}, {"id": 55580, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "11867670"}, {"id": 55581, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no90026193"}, {"id": 55582, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no90026193"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T00:19:33.410573+10:00"}, {"id": 75016, "name": "Ward Kimball", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 854975, "title": "Man in space", "work_id": 70083, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1914-03-04", "date_of_death": "2002-07-08", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 1, "name": "United States of America", "slug": "united-states-of-america"}], "biography": "Ward Walrath Kimball (March 4, 1914 – July 8, 2002) was an American animator employed by Walt Disney Animation Studios. He was part of Walt Disney's main team of animators, known collectively as Disney's Nine Old Men. His films have been honored with two Academy Awards for Best Animated Short Film.\nOutside of his job as an animator, Kimball was a railroad enthusiast as well as a talented jazz trombonist. He founded and led the seven-piece Dixieland band Firehouse Five Plus Two, in which he played the trombone.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-06T02:11:37.969154+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 6248, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ward_Kimball"}], "uuid": "a45fc617-7e33-44dd-b321-4fd4be588605", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": null, "external_references": [{"id": 50562, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q2118269"}, {"id": 56050, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "35071253"}, {"id": 56051, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "nr00021398"}, {"id": 56052, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-nr00021398"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T02:11:40.913939+10:00"}, {"id": 75015, "name": "Graeme Ferguson", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 857414, "title": "The Question of television violence", "work_id": 71999, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2645552, "title": "Man belongs to the earth", "work_id": 70080, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "Ivan Graeme Ferguson", "date_of_birth": "1929-10-07", "date_of_death": "2021-05-08", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 36, "name": "Canada", "slug": "canada"}], "biography": "Ivan Graeme Ferguson  (October 7, 1929 – May 8, 2021) was a Canadian filmmaker and inventor who co-invented the IMAX film format.  He was appointed to the Order of Canada in 1992.; 17/08/2023", "biography_author": nu